HEADWORD: Recognition
<hw>Rec`og*ni"tion</hw> <pr>(r⟦ecr⟧k`⟦ocr⟧g*n⟦icr⟧sh"⟦ucr⟧n)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>recognitio</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>recognition</ets>. See <er>Recognizance</er>.]</ety> <def>The act
of recognizing, or the state of being recognized; acknowledgment; formal
avowal; knowledge confessed or avowed; notice.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The lives of such saints had, at the time of their yearly
memorials, solemn <qex>recognition</qex> in the church of God.</q>
<rj><qau>Hooker.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Recognitor</ent>⟦br⟧
